DCB Commercial Bank has launched ‘Skonga Club’ to provide education to account holders about benefits of saving for the future of their children.  The DCB Managing Director, Godfrey Ndalahwa said at the launch of the club in Dar es Salaam at the weekend that DCB was urging customers to join the club by just opening the education account. “DCB Skonga Club has been launched as an offshoot of DCB Skonga, to add value to its customers including parents, guardians and children,” he said stressing that, parents should utilise and benefit from the service by opening DCB Skonga Account as the bank celebrates its 20th anniversary since its establishment. The launching of the Skonga club was in tandem with achievements registered since introducing the Skonga Account in September 2019, to guarantee child education up to the university level. Mr Ndalahwa with Skonga Club, parents and guardians are entitled to the VISA credit card, school fees loans, emergency loan of up to 90 per cent of the deposited amount, financial education for the children, counselling of children, joining the special programme for financial and investment issues and various sports. He said that Skonga Club members will be entitled to attend various events including exchange of ideas, leadership programme and get discount rates for goods and services from business partners who have entered an agreement with the bank like hotels, playing courts for children and national parks. “DCB Skonga Club is full of economic, education and recreational benefits for children and parents because via this club children will get information on various schools, employment exhibitions, link with DCB programmes for employment of graduates, and on top of that attend training on entrepreneurship that will be offered by our bank,” he said. Skonga Club is a place to make new friends and to make historic events in sports, education and financial issues, life skills, at the same time we work to identify and nurture child talents.